<row valign="top">
<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Unit 3 Essay Activity:</emphasis><newline/><emphasis effect="bold">Was the democratization of politics during the Jacksonian era a shift from Founding era political theory?</emphasis><newline/><emphasis effect="bold">Option B: Evaluate the extent to which the democratization of politics during the Jacksonian Era was a change from Founding era political theory.</emphasis><newline/>Through this inquiry, students will evaluate primary and secondary sources to compare the expansion of democracy in the Jacksonian period to the ideals of the American Founding, drawing on context and content from this as well as previous chapters. Ultimately, students will be able to practice a change-and-continuity Long Essay Question (LEQ) comparing how political ideals shifted and persevered in America from the Founding through the Jacksonian era. Assess students‚Äô progress in understanding the compelling question for this chapter by assigning the <link class="target-chapter" document="m79386">Unit 3 Essay Activity</link>.</entry>
